14/10/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The commander of NATO Headquarters in Skopje, Brigadier General Dennis Blease, said Wednesday (13 October) that implementation of the Ohrid Peace Accords and reforms were essential prerequisites for the country's entry into NATO. Blease, who also heads the NATO advisory team in Macedonia, told a news conference that Skopje might be offered an invitation in the next enlargement wave, if reforms continue. 
In other news, a new survey conducted by the Macedonian government and USAID suggests broad public dissatisfaction with the performance of local governments. Most complaints involved unemployment and poor infrastructure. (Utrinski Vesnik, Vest - 14/10/04; A1 TV, Makfax - 13/10/04) 
